Today we're diving into one of the most controversial documentaries ever made about the death of Princess Diana — Unlawful Killing by Keith Allen. Banned in the UK and buried from public release, the film claims a royal cover-up, points fingers at the British establishment, and includes testimony from Mohamed Al-Fayed himself. As we watch along, we’ll unpack the claims, question the evidence, and explore what this film says about power, censorship, and the legacy of Diana.
